      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIGHTNING RANGE (1) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2.25 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.08 beating Paw Razor. Nicely placed here on the inside and goes well at this distance. Has a solid record from this box including six wins and a minor placing. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. LEKTRA AELA (7) missed the frame latest when fifth at this track (22.48) but scored five back at Horsham (23.59). Has a good record here at this journey. The form out of last race has been strong. Expected to give a good account. PRINCESS DOMI (6) won again in an impressive display after enjoying a good run making it three straight, scoring at Shepparton over 390m (22.71). Has put together a string of wins and expected to go close again. SEATS TWO (4) is building a nice sequence of placings – hard to fault that form.",
